<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1858,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1858,1884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Abdominal tergite 
<number box="[508,523,1859,1885]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
with yellowish lateral hairs, tergites 
<number box="[958,1003,1859,1885]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
with yellowish hairs antero-laterally and tergites 
<number box="[295,340,1898,1924]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
with yellowish hairs posteriorly. Epiphallus widely clubbed, with a round tip in dorsal view, distiphallus short in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1858,2001]" box="[197,989,1975,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,1975,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body length 
<quantity box="[582,697,1975,2001]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[854,985,1975,2001]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189087/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" targetBox="[164,1426,207,1435]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1483,1575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,337,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">FIGURES 6–11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[344,604,1483,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Heteralonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anemosyris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[344,604,1483,1506]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Heteralonia anemosyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[612,699,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[612,699,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male genitalia. 6. epandrium and cercus, dorsal view; 7. epandrium and cercus, lateral view; 8. gonocoxa and gonostylus, lateral view; 9. phallus, dorsal view; 10. phallus, lateral view; 11. gonocoxae and gonostyli, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1622,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Head black with brown pollen; ocellar tubercle black. Hairs on head mostly black; frons with erect black hairs, face with dense erect black hairs; occiput with short black hairs and sparse yellowish scales, and with dense erect black hairs on edge. Antenna black; scape nearly three times longer than wide, with dense long black hairs; pedicel nearly as long as wide, with short black hairs; first flagellomere cone-shaped, bare, with a stylus two-segmented, and slightly longer than first flagellomere. Antennal ratio: 
<number box="[1114,1133,1777,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
: 
<number box="[1139,1153,1777,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[1158,1177,1777,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
. Proboscis black with short black hairs; palpus dark brown with black hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1622,2035]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,152,332]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Thorax black with grey pollen. Hairs on thorax black and yellowish, bristles black; postpronotal lobe with long black hairs, mesonotum with row of long yellowish hairs at anterior margin and two long black lateral bristles near base of wing, postalar callus with four black bristles. Scutellum with black scales on anterior edge and with yellow scales on posterior edge. Legs black with black scales. Hairs on legs mostly black, bristles black. Femora with sparse long black hairs; tibiae and tarsi with short black hairs. Mid femur with three 
<emphasis box="[218,246,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">av</emphasis>
apically; hind femur with seven 
<emphasis box="[640,668,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">av</emphasis>
apically. Mid tibia with seven 
<emphasis box="[1037,1066,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">ad</emphasis>
, eight 
<emphasis box="[1150,1179,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">pd</emphasis>
, six 
<emphasis box="[1237,1265,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">av</emphasis>
and seven 
<emphasis box="[1400,1428,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">pv</emphasis>
; hind tibia with seven 
<emphasis box="[428,459,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">ad</emphasis>
, seven 
<emphasis box="[558,589,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">pd</emphasis>
, seven 
<emphasis box="[687,716,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">av</emphasis>
and eight 
<emphasis box="[853,881,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">pv</emphasis>
. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[985,1062,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1582,1606]" captionTargetBox="[152,1424,901,1538]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,894,1557]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Heteralonia wings. 1. Heteralonia anemosyris sp. nov.; 2. Heteralonia cnecos sp. nov.; 3. Heteralonia nigripilosa sp. nov.; 4. Heteralonia ochros sp. nov.; 5. Heteralonia sytshuana (Paramonov)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189086/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1045,1062,190,216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with mostly infuscate, paler posteriorly; vein dm-cu with two spur-veins nearly same in length, directed basally and distally; wing with dark brown spots near all cross veins. Base of vein C with brush-like long black hairs. Wing with basicosta strong; vein r-m nearly at middle of discal cell. Halteres brown except tip yellowish.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189088/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" targetBox="[159,1431,390,1488]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1524,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,353,1524,1548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">FIGURES 12–17.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[360,572,1525,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Heteralonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cnecos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[360,572,1525,1548]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Heteralonia cnecos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[580,667,1524,1548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[580,667,1524,1548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male genitalia. 12. epandrium and cercus, dorsal view; 13. epandrium and cercus, lateral view; 14. gonocoxa and gonostylus, lateral view; 15. phallus, dorsal view; 16. phallus, lateral view; 17. gonocoxae and gonostyli, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1664,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Abdomen black. Hairs on abdomen black and white; dorsum with dense long black hairs laterally except tergite 
<number box="[234,249,1702,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
with yellowish hairs laterally; dorsum with dense black recumbent scales, except tergites 
<number box="[1330,1375,1702,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
with yellowish hairs antero-laterally and tergites 
<number box="[677,722,1741,1767]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
with yellowish hairs on posterior edge. Sternites with erect black hairs and dense recumbent black scales.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1664,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[385,532,1818,1844]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,271,1524,1548]" captionTargetBox="[159,1431,390,1488]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,390,1499]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 17. Heteralonia cnecos sp. nov. male genitalia. 12. epandrium and cercus, dorsal view; 13. epandrium and cercus, lateral view; 14. gonocoxa and gonostylus, lateral view; 15. phallus, dorsal view; 16. phallus, lateral view; 17. gonocoxae and gonostyli, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189088/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Figs. 
<number box="[453,532,1818,1844]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="14.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="12.0">12–17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium subtriangular, with long black bristles apically, slightly higher than long; cercus well exposed in lateral view; epandrium subquadrate, nearly as long as wide in dorsal view; gonocoxae with many black hairs apically, distinctly narrowing apically in ventral view; gonostylus thick at base, acute at tip and slightly curved at middle in lateral view; epiphallus widely clubbed, with a round tip in dorsal view, distiphallus short in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1664,2037]" box="[197,421,2011,2037]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
