<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,562]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,339,305,331]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet derives from the Greek “knekos” means “pale-yellow”; referring to the yellowish hairs on abdominal dorsum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,562]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,382,408]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Paramonov" authorityName="Paramonov" box="[680,979,382,408]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Heteralonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sytshuana">
<emphasis box="[680,835,382,407]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">H. sytshuana</emphasis>
Paramonov
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated from the latter by the following features: wing mostly infuscate, hyaline just at tip; abdominal dorsum with tergites 
<number box="[1332,1376,420,446]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
with yellowish hairs antero-laterally and tergites 
<number box="[673,718,459,485]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
with yellowish hairs on posterior edge. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1229,1384,459,484]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Heteralonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sytshuana">
<emphasis box="[1229,1384,459,484]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">H. sytshuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the wing is partly infuscate, hyaline posteriorly; the abdominal dorsum has the dense long black hairs laterally except tergite 
<number box="[316,331,536,562]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1.0">1</number>
with the yellowish hairs laterally and with the dense black recumbent scales.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
